# Kaappi Book Project Rules

## Project Context

This is a XeLaTeX book about the Kaappi Scheme programming language. The target audience is beginners who know another language like Python. The book is compiled with XeLaTeX using the memoir document class.

## Build

- Build command: `make` (runs 3 XeLaTeX passes for TOC/index resolution)
- Quick single pass: `make once`
- Output: `build/main.pdf`
- Engine: XeLaTeX only (fontspec requires it)

## Writing Style

- Write for programmers who know Python but not Scheme or Lisp
- Avoid academic jargon; explain concepts through code examples
- Use active voice and short sentences
- Every new concept should have a runnable code example
- Compare to Python equivalents when it aids understanding
- Introduce one concept at a time; build on previous chapters

## LaTeX Conventions

- Chapter files live in `chapters/` and are `\input{}` from `main.tex`
- Use `\begin{lstlisting}` for Scheme code blocks (configured in `preamble/listings.tex`)
- Use `\lstinline{...}` or `\code{...}` for inline code
- Use `\begin{note}` for informational callouts
- Use `\begin{warning}` for pitfalls and common mistakes
- Use `\begin{exercise}` for end-of-chapter practice problems
- Use `\begin{codeoutput}` for showing REPL session output
- Use `\sectionbreak` between major topic transitions within a chapter
- Use `\chapterend` at the end of chapters (before exercises if any)
- Do NOT use `\lstset` in chapter files; global config is in `preamble/listings.tex`
- Do NOT add packages in chapter files; all packages are in `preamble/packages.tex`

## Code Examples

- Scheme code uses the `lstlisting` environment (default style is `scheme`)
- REPL sessions use `\begin{lstlisting}[style=repl]`
- Show the `> ` prompt for REPL input lines
- Show output on lines without the prompt
- Keep examples short (under 20 lines); split longer ones into steps

## File Organization

- One chapter per file in `chapters/`
- Preamble is modular: edit the specific file in `preamble/` for style changes
- Fonts are bundled in `fonts/` (EB Garamond, Source Sans 3, Fira Code)
- Never commit build artifacts; they are gitignored

## Reference Material

- Kaappi source code: `/Users/bmuthuka/kaappi/kaappi`
- Kaappi website docs: `/Users/bmuthuka/kaappi/kaappi.github.io`
- Use these as authoritative sources for Kaappi behavior and features
